      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(android): enable SMS/MMS for Play flavor + fix MMS query timeout",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nEnables SMS/MMS access in the Android Play flavor build and fixes a critical timeout in MMS query hydration.\n\n### Changes\n\n**Enable SMS/MMS for Play flavor**\n- `app/build.gradle.kts`: Set `OPENCLAW_ENABLE_SMS=true` and `OPENCLAW_ENABLE_CALL_LOG=true` for the Play product flavor (previously `false` for Play Store compliance, now enabled for self-hosted builds)\n- `app/src/play/AndroidManifest.xml`: Remove `tools:node=\"remove\"` directives that were stripping `SEND_SMS`, `READ_SMS`, and `READ_CALL_LOG` permissions from the Play flavor manifest\n- `SettingsSheet.kt` / `OnboardingFlow.kt`: Update SMS label to \"SMS / MMS\" and clarify description covers both send, search, and read for SMS and MMS\n\n**Fix MMS query timeout**\n- `SmsManager.kt`: Rewrote `querySmsMmsMessagesByPhone` to use two-phase batch MMS hydration instead of per-row content resolver queries\n\n**Before:** O(n×3) individual queries per MMS row (getMmsAddress + getMmsTextBody + getMmsMeta per row) → hangs past 30s gateway timeout on large message histories\n\n**After:**\n- Phase 1: Fast cursor pass collecting all rows without sub-queries, stashing MMS IDs needing hydration\n- Phase 2: Batch query `content://mms/part` (single query for all text bodies) + batch query `content://mms` (single query for all msg_box/read meta)\n- Cap: max 50 MMS rows hydrated per query (most recent first)\n- `withTimeout(25_000L)` wrapper for graceful failure instead of indefinite hang\n\n### Testing\n- SMS search works immediately after granting `READ_SMS` permission\n- MMS search with `includeMms: true` completes within timeout on large message histories\n- `sms.send` and `sms.read` added to gateway `allowCommands`",
